<ContentLayout
  eyebrow="About"
  title="What this site is"
  description="A private place for our growing family."
>
  <p>
    A week-by-week guide for our little one alongside a small journal of moments as they happen.
    The site is password-protected and shared only with close family and friends.
  </p>

  <h2>The guide</h2>
  <p>
    Each week's page pulls together the things that seem to matter for that stage:
    developmental milestones, practical to-dos, feeding and sleep guidance, and clear
    "when to call the pediatrician" signals. Content is drawn from pediatric sources
    (Canadian Paediatric Society, AAP, HealthLinkBC) and always links back to them.
  </p>
  <p>
    This is a personal record, not medical advice. If something feels wrong, call your
    pediatrician. Alberta HealthLink is <strong>811</strong>; in an emergency call <strong>911</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>The journal</h2>
  <p>
    Short reflections and moments — dictated loosely and polished into something readable.
    Written mostly for us, and for the small circle we're happy to share this with.
  </p>
</ContentLayout>
